description.value: Egyptian blue scarab. Finely modelled scarab, with high back, legs well modelled with deeply undercut triangle, and much broader, rounder shape than usual. Back has clearly deliniated clypeus, prothorax border with double incised line, elytra divided by triple line- double suture. Feathering shown clearly on forelegs. Pierced longitudinally. Base decorated with square pellet border inside which are  two deeply cut out figures of animals. The upper one, with four legs and a heavy tail, must be a lion, the lower one is a helpless victim, herbivore, a boar(?) on its back.  Blue paste is hard, greyish blue with a glossy finish.
